            <div class="extract">
               <div class="original">
                  <span class="label">By Ben Jonson</span>
                  <blockquote>
                     <p>Come Sweet Caelia let us prove <br>While we may y<sup>e</sup> sports of Love <br>Time will not be o<sup>rs</sup> for ever <br>He at length o<sup>r</sup> blisse will sever <br>Spen not then his giftes in vaine <br>Suns that set, may rise againe. <br>But if we once loose this light <br>It's w<sup>th</sup> us perpetuall night <br>Why should we defer o<sup>r</sup> joys <br>Fame, &amp; Rumour, are but toyes. <br>Cannote we delude the eyes? <br>Of a few poore household spyes. <br>And his easier eares beguile, <br>Soe remov'd by many a mile. <br>It's no sinne loves fruits to steale, <br>But the sweet thefts to reveale. <br>To be taken, to be <del>sene</del>seene&gt; <br>These hath crimes accounted beene.</p>
