               <div class="original">
                  <span class="label">Verses before a Masque</span>
                  <blockquote>
                     <p>Gentlemen y’are welcome, but not from me, <br>For god’s my judge, doe but let you see <br>Men; whom of late, from out y<sup>e</sup> Northerns sands <br>The sea belcht up, upon our fruitfull lands, <br>They are all males, put yo<sup>u</sup> but females to’um <br>They will not sticke in baudy termes to woo 'um <br>I brought them hither for to make yo<sup>u</sup> sport <br>And when that’s done we’le whip them to y<sup>e</sup> court. <br>They’re skill’d in horne-pipes, Jigs, &amp; country-rounds <br>God save King James, the divell take his hounds.</p>
